title: unprocessed whole milk from donor A
treatment_protocol_ch1: HPP samples: subjected to HPP in 62.5°C for 30 minutes in Human Milk Pasteurizer S90 Eco (Sterifeed, Medicare Colgate Ltd, England, Cullompton). HoP samples: HoP using U 4000/65 apparatus (Unipress Equipment, Poland, Celestynow). Control samples: untreated. Storage: frozen at -20°C before further processing.
extract_protocol_ch1: Serum/Plasma Advanced Kit (Qiagen), according to manufacturers instructions.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: QIAseq miRNA Library Kit (Qiagen), according to manufacturers instructions.
data_processing: Read adapters were trimmed and UMI sequences were extracted by UMI-tools v1.0.0. Maximum 2bp mismatch in a 19bp-long adapter sequence (AACTGTAGGCACCATCAAT) was allowed. Reads with incomplete UMI sequence (<12nt) and shorter than 15bp after trimming were excluded from the downstream analyses.
data_processing.1: Trimmed reads were mapped to miRBase v22 mature human miRNA sequences. Prior to mapping, mature miRNA records with identical sequences were collapsed to allow unique mapping. Bowtie2 v2.3.4.1 local alignment with following parameters was used: “-N1 -L9 --norc -k10 --local --score-min L,4,1.3 --mp 4”. Reads mapping to multiple miRNAs with equal scores were excluded. Uniquely mapped reads were deduplicated based on UMI using the “unique" method in UMI-tools. Next, SAMtools v1.9 idxstats was used to obtain read counts for each miRNA. The counts are in mirna_count_matrix.txt
data_processing.3: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab delimited matrix of miRBase mapping read counts
contact_department: Department of Biostatistics and Translational Medicine

HoP samples: HoP using U 4000/65 apparatus (Unipress Equipment, Poland, Celestynow). Control samples: untreated. Storage: frozen at -20°C before further processing.
extract_protocol_ch1: miRCURY Exosome Cell/Urine/CSF Kit (Qiagen, Hilden, Germany), according to manufacturers instructions.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Serum/Plasma Advanced Kit (Qiagen), according to manufacturers instructions.
extract_protocol_ch1.2: QIAseq miRNA Library Kit (Qiagen), according to manufacturers instructions.
data_processing: Read adapters were trimmed and UMI sequences were extracted by UMI-tools v1.0.0. Maximum 2bp mismatch in a 19bp-long adapter sequence (AACTGTAGGCACCATCAAT) was allowed. Reads with incomplete UMI sequence (<12nt) and shorter than 15bp after trimming were excluded from the downstream analyses.
data_processing.1: Trimmed reads were mapped to miRBase v22 mature human miRNA sequences. Prior to mapping, mature miRNA records with identical sequences were collapsed to allow unique mapping. Bowtie2 v2.3.4.1 local alignment with following parameters was used: “-N1 -L9 --norc -k10 --local --score-min L,4,1.3 --mp 4”. Reads mapping to multiple miRNAs with equal scores were excluded. Uniquely mapped reads were deduplicated based on UMI using the “unique" method in UMI-tools. Next, SAMtools v1.9 idxstats was used to obtain read counts for each miRNA. The counts are in mirna_count_matrix.txt
data_processing.3: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab delimited matrix of miRBase mapping read counts
contact_department: Department of Biostatistics and Translational Medicine
